<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4631801>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 10. Nectoneanthes uchiwa sp. nov. (A, B) Holotype (NSMT Pol H-549): (A) dorsal view of the whole body; (B) dorsal view of anterior end with everted proboscis. (C–E) Non-type atoke (NSMT-Pol 11408) collected from the mouth of Midori-kawa River in Ariake Sea, anterior end with the everted proboscis: (C) dorsal view; (D) ventral view; (E) lateral view (left side). (F, G) Non-type epitokes collected from the mouth of Omuta-gawa River, Ariake Sea, dorsal views of prostomium: (F) female (NSMT-Pol 11409); (G) male (NSMT-Pol 11410). Seven groups of paragnaths in different areas on proboscis are shown as I to VII–VIII. Arrow indicates a few rows of paragnaths of group VII–VIII in a lateral side. Scale bars, 10 mm in A; 1 mm in B–G." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4631801/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4631789>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 4. Schematic diagrams of atokous chaetal arrangement in distal view of right parapodium around chaetiger 50 in adults. (A) Nectoneanthes oxypoda and Nectoneanthes uchiwa sp. nov. (B) Neanthes succinea. Closed circles: homogomph or sesquigomph spinigers. Closed squares: heterogomph spinigers. Closed stars: heterogomph falcigers. Abbreviations same as for those in Figure 3." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4631789/files/figure.png" .

